The paper deals with the problem of sequence mappability, which involves computing a table of values for a given sequence. This problem is related to data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and algorithms (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper presents several efficient algorithms, which involves analyzing the running time and space complexity, making it relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
